                        SERVER CREATION OF E-COMMERCE
1   create package .json file - npm init
2   create  node modules - install express -npm i express                 
3   create index.js (main entry point)
4   In Index.js
             1)import express
             2)create an application using express
             3)setup a portnumber
             4)use json parser for server responses
5   Integration 
             1)install cors -npm i cors
             2)import cors into index.js
             3)using cors specify the origin to the server
               origin:'http://localhost:4200'
6   Services - create a folder Service - create a folder service also create 2 files 
              1)dataservice.js
              2)db.js
7   backend and mongodb connection
              1)install mongoose - npm i mongoose
              2)import mongoose into db.js
              3)define the connection string
              4)create model for products and export it
8   resolving API calls in index.js
              1)import dataservices
9   create logic in dataservice
              1)import db
              2) define function
10  Final step define api calls in index.js


